# T-2160 — substrate-preflight nightly canary (PL-021 + hubs.toml + be-reachable
# deploy-time validation; complement of release-mirror-canary).
#
# Source of truth: /opt/termlink/.context/cron/substrate-preflight-canary.crontab (git-tracked)
# Installed to:    /etc/cron.d/termlink-substrate-preflight-canary (USER field syntax — do NOT load into a user crontab)
#
# Daily check that the substrate environment is still correctly configured
# AFTER any host reboot, container restart, package upgrade, or systemd unit
# change. Catches PL-021 regressions (a fresh /tmp wipe re-introduces the
# volatile-runtime-dir failure mode if the migration was lost), missing
# hubs.toml after a /root rebuild, and dead be-reachable state files.
#
# Exit 0 from --quiet means PASS; the log accumulates only when something
# is wrong, so an empty log is the healthy state.
#
# Diagnostic on log entry: read the framed block (each event starts with
# === YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ === and ends with ---) — it contains the same
# output `/preflight` would have shown interactively.
#
# Operator action: see CLAUDE.md §"Hub Auth Rotation Protocol" → "Special
# case — volatile runtime_dir" for the runtime_dir failure path; see
# `docs/operations/substrate-orchestrator-recipe.md` § "Deployment &
# identity troubleshooting" for the broader failure-mode catalog.
SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# Daily at 05:23 UTC — offset chosen to avoid colliding with :13 mirror
# canary, :17 heartbeat, :33 meta-canary, and :43 rollout audit. Runs as
# root so cwd-into the repo doesn't trip permissions and so it can read
# /usr/lib/tmpfiles.d/ (Check 1 needs that for the systemd-tmpfiles D-rule
# detection — non-root execution would silently downgrade Check 1 to
# "tmpfs-only" coverage).
23 5 * * * root cd /opt/termlink && bash scripts/substrate-preflight.sh --quiet >> .context/working/.substrate-preflight-canary.log 2>&1
